<br>
With Luclin, more than one thing was all kinds of fucked up and I'm pretty sure that this is what happened with Velious and Kunark.<br>
<br>
Take the pickbringer's coifs for example. It was assigned an item number on loot tables that was identical to something else (probably a piece of cloth armor or a specific rusty weapon) that was on the general orc/gnoll loot tables. This is a vendor item from shadowhaven (like chainmail armor in qeynos) and shouldn't be dropping at all from these creatures (it vendors for 25pp).<br>
<br>
Another set of wonders: the Drop rates in ToV and Kael changing CONSTANTLY. Someone isn't paying attention when a coder changes a number and BAM, drop numbers fall into the basement. Or in Velks and (allegedly) sleeper's.. .where very high level mobs are dropping cloth caps and slippers.... another mis-assigned number.<br>
<br>
This isn't a bait and switch marketing issue to me, this is a quality control issue. <p>Nakath<BR>
